# NestJS Architecture

- **Module boundaries:** Every feature gets its own module (`*.module.ts`). Never import services directly across features — use the module's `exports`.
- **Thin controllers:** Controllers only handle HTTP concerns (routing, status codes, extracting params). All business logic belongs in the service layer.
- **DTOs for everything:** Use a dedicated DTO class for every request body and response shape. Never accept or return plain objects.
- **Barrel exports:** Each module folder should have an `index.ts` re-exporting its public API.

```ts
// ❌ BAD — logic in controller
@Post()
async create(@Body() body: { name: string }) {
  return this.db.save({ name: body.name.trim().toLowerCase() });
}

// ✅ GOOD — delegate to service
@Post()
async create(@Body() dto: CreateUserDto): Promise<UserResponseDto> {
  return this.userService.create(dto);
}
```
